UNITED STATES of America v. C. G. HOWLAND, Proponent of the Last Will and Testament of George G. Johnnie, Deceased. No. 1676. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 4, 1938. Charles N. Champion, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Muskogee, Okl., for appellant. J. E. Williams, of Ardmore, Old., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, on motion of appellant.
